sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: H/E-rev
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Holin/endolysin reversed - RBS and double T7 terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Holin and endolysin are toxins; after a period of late-gene expression, holin, an inner permeabilizing protein creates holes in the membrane in order to permeabilize it and then endolysin, a muralytic enzyme traverses the holes creating by holin and degraded the wall cell. This complex induce cell lysis of bacteria. (Young & Bl??si, 1995)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Johanna Chesnel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: BBa_K1616005 is a composite part with BBa_K1616006 (endolysin reversed), BBa_K1616007 (reversed), BBa_K1616011 (RBS reversed) and BBa_B0025 (Double terminator T7 reversed).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: End-rev
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Holin and endolysin are toxins; after a period of late-gene expression, holin, an inner permeabilizing protein creates holes in the membrane in order to permeabilize it and then endolysin, a muralytic enzyme traverses the holes creating by holin and degraded the wall cell. This complex induce cell lysis of bacteria. (Young & Bl??si, 1995)

This part is the sequence reverse of the Holin/ Endolysin; thus this part can be used with a reverse promoter. Young, R., & Bl??si, U. (1995). Holins: Form and function in bacteriophage lysis. In FEMS Microbiology Reviews (Vol. 17, pp. 191???205). http://doi.org/10.1016/01686445(94)00079-4

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RBS-rev
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: For more efficiency of construction, scientists use more and more reversed promoter and then reversed sequences of proteins coding. This part have been created in order to recruit transcriptional machinery and lead to transcritpion of the upstream DNA sequence. So, this part is the reverse sequence of the BBa_I712074 promoter T7.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Johanna Chesnel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is the reverse sequence of the BBa_I712074 promoter T7.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We have checked that any illegal sites was formed.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Holin-rev
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Holin works with endolysin; they create a toxic system, after a period of late-gene expression, holin, an inner permeabilizing protein creates holes in the membrane in order to permeabilize it and then endolysin, a muralytic enzyme traverses the holes creating by holin and degraded the wall cell. This complex induce cell lysis of bacteria. (Young & Bl??si, 1995)
This part is the reversed sequence of the holin (BBa_K112805); thus this part can be used with a reversed endolysin (BBa_K1616006), reversed promoter, reversed RBS and reversed terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Johanna Chesnel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is the reverses sequence of the BBa_K112805 (Holin).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The illegal sites have been checked
